### Complete HTML Code

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Random Joke Generator</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            text-align: center;
            padding-top: 50px;
            background-color: #f0f0f0;
        }
        #joke {
            margin-top: 20px;
            font-size: 1.2em;
            color: #333;
        }
        button {
            padding: 10px 20px;
            font-size: 1em;
            cursor: pointer;
            background-color: #4CAF50;
            color: white;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }
        button:hover {
            background-color: #45a049;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Random Joke Generator</h1>
    <button onclick="showJoke()">Tell me a joke</button>
    <div id="joke"></div>

    <script>
        // List of jokes
        const jokes = [
            "Why don't scientists trust atoms? Because they make up everything!",
            "I told my computer I needed a break, and it said 'No problem — I'll go to sleep.'",
            "Why did the scarecrow win an award? Because he was outstanding in his field!",
            "I would tell you a construction pun, but I'm still working on it."
        ];

        // Function to display a random joke
        function showJoke() {
            // Generate a random index based on the jokes array length
            const randomIndex = Math.floor(Math.random() * jokes.length);
            // Display the selected joke in the #joke div
            document.getElementById('joke').innerText = jokes[randomIndex];
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

### How It Works

1. **HTML Structure**
    - **`<h1>` Tag**: Displays the title "Random Joke Generator".
    - **`<button>` Element**: When clicked, it triggers the `showJoke()` function.
    - **`<div id="joke">`**: This is where the selected joke will be displayed.

2. **Styling with CSS**
    - Centers the content and adds some padding and background color for better aesthetics.
    - Styles the button with colors, padding, and hover effects to make it more interactive.

3. **JavaScript Functionality**
    - **Jokes Array**: Contains four different jokes.
    - **`showJoke()` Function**:
        - Generates a random index between 0 and the length of the jokes array.
        - Uses this index to select a joke from the array.
        - Displays the selected joke inside the `<div>` with the id `joke`.

### How to Use

1. **Create an HTML File**
    - Open a text editor (like Notepad, VS Code, Sublime Text, etc.).
    - Copy and paste the complete HTML code provided above into the editor.
    - Save the file with a `.html` extension, for example, `joke-generator.html`.

2. **Open in a Web Browser**
    - Locate the saved HTML file on your computer.
    - Double-click the file to open it in your default web browser.
    - You should see the "Random Joke Generator" title, a button labeled "Tell me a joke," and an area where jokes will appear.

3. **Generate Jokes**
    - Click the "Tell me a joke" button.
    - A random joke from the list will appear below the button.
    - Click the button again to see another joke.

